						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ••••••Year: 1418, <hi rend="italic">Durmati, Kārttigai 18.</hi></hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged at the end. It records a gift of land, including two wells, as <hi rend="italic">kāṇiyāttchi</hi> in Murugamaṅgalam by Tirumalai-Nāyakkar and Īśura-Nāyakkar to the Tirumalāruḍaiyār temple at Dēvakkāpuram in Palkuṉṟa-kkōṭṭam (a sub division of) Jayaṅgoṇḍachōḻamaṇḍalam, for providing incence during the twilight service <hi rend="italic">(vandikāppu)</hi> and on other auspicious days. Also provides for the anointment of the deity and for the paste <hi rend="italic">(tiruchchāndu).</hi></p>						

						</summary>
